## 🚀 Quick Start

1. Start a container of the pre-built runtime image.
    ```bash
    docker run --rm -it {{ container_image }} bash
    ```
1. Inside the container, launch the pre-built nodes.
    ```bash
    ros2 launch {{ quickstart_package }} {{ quickstart_launch_file }}
    ```

## 🧑‍💻 Development

### Set up Development Environment

1. Clone the repository.
    ```bash
    git clone {{ repo_https_url }}.git
    ```
1. Initialize the [`.openads-dev-environment`](https://github.com/openads-project/openads-dev-environment) submodule containing development environment configuration.
    ```bash
    cd {{ repo_name }}
    git submodule update --init --recursive
    ```
1. Open the repository in [Visual Studio Code](https://code.visualstudio.com).
    ```bash
    code .
    ```
1. Install the recommended VS Code extensions.
    > *Ctrl+Shift+P / Extensions: Show Recommended Extensions / Install Workspace Recommended Extensions (Cloud Download Icon)*
1. Reopen the repository in a [Dev Container](https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/devcontainers/containers).
    > *Ctrl+Shift+P / Dev Containers: Rebuild and Reopen in Container*

### Build

> *Ctrl+Shift+B*

```bash
colcon build
```

### Run Tests

> *Ctrl+Shift+P / Tasks: Run Test Task*

```bash
colcon build --cmake-args -DCMAKE_EXPORT_COMPILE_COMMANDS=1
colcon test
colcon test-result --verbose
```


